        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: inbound metadata leakage — missing sentinels and display gaps",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nInbound metadata leakage into user-visible chat\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/strip-inbound-meta.ts`: Fix applied. See commit diff for details.\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/strip-inbound-meta.test.ts`: Add 4 regression tests for lookalike user text\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Inbound metadata leakage into user-visible chat\n\nReal environment tested: ubuntu-24.04, Node 24, branch fix/issue-93966-metadata-leakage.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n  node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/strip-inbound-meta.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/strip-inbound-meta.test.ts\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n ✓ 39 tests passed (39)\n\n Includes 4 new regression tests for lookalike user text:\n ✓ does not strip user text starting with 'Current message:'\n ✓ does not strip user text containing (untrusted, ...) pattern\n ✓ does not strip leading text with metadata-like context\n ✓ does not strip parenthetical annotations that are not metadata\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  39 passed (39)\n   Duration  681ms\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: All 39 strip-inbound-meta tests pass, including 4 new regression tests that verify ordinary user text resembling metadata patterns is not incorrectly stripped. Code change resolves the reported leakage while the additional tests narrow the non-fenced metadata handling.\n\nWhat was not tested: End-to-end with real multi-channel credentials.\n\nCloses: #93966",
